Class TargetBase

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.friendlysnmp.target.TargetBase
  • Direct Known Subclasses:
    TargetV1, TargetV3

    public abstract class TargetBase
extends java.lang.Object
    This class is a base class for SNMP v2 and v3 targets.

      • getTargetAddrName

        protected org.snmp4j.smi.OctetString getTargetAddrName()
        The method creates read-only "Name" for the column snmpTargetAddrName in the table snmpTargetMIB.snmpTargetAddrTable. This name could be any unique. See description in the MIB: "The locally arbitrary, but unique identifier associated with this snmpTargetAddrEntry."
        Returns:
        OctetString

      • getTargetParamsName

        protected org.snmp4j.smi.OctetString getTargetParamsName()
        The method creates read-only "Name" which is used in two places linking them:
        1. Column snmpTargetParamsName in the table snmpTargetMIB.snmpTargetParamsTable
        2. Column snmpTargetAddrParams in the table snmpTargetMIB.snmpTargetAddrTable

        The name could be any unique. See description in the MIB for these two tables. MIB Params table: "The locally arbitrary, but unique identifier associated with this snmpTargetParamsEntry."
        MIB Addr table: "The value of this object identifies an entry in the snmpTargetParamsTable. The identified entry contains SNMP parameters to be used when generating messages to be sent to this transport address."
        Returns:
        OctetString
